		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform" ><span class="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=411896"><span id="Scholar">Chevydiabolos</span></a><b><span id="Scholar"><br>Scholar</span></b><br /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><br />68 posts
		   <br /><nobr><span class="notbold">Score</span>: Good [3.62]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Chevydiabolos&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%">
<p>Okay so I did my first Ballista last night. I have been playing since the NA release on PC but never really fealt the need to do Ballista. My boy Mrcrabs is always doing it and asking me to come so last night I decided to go with him for the first time. I was lvling my 20rdm and was bored anyway so I jumped on my 62RNG/NIN and headed to Meriphataud Mountain (sp?). The ballista was a 60 cap and both sides had 8 players. OMG as soon as this thing started I just got excited. I just ran around picking on all the mages and thiefs (what is morefun then one-shotting a 60rdm or 60thf?). Anyway, it was great fun. We won the first match, lost the second, and won the third. So after it was all done we won the 2/3 match.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br /> <br />I know many of you have done Ballista before, some maybe many times and thinking &quot;Whats the big deal?&quot;. Forme, someone who was just getting tired of the day-in-day-out rigors of lvl then farm then lvl then farm then lvl then farm, it brought a whole new fun into the game. To all of you people who are up and coming or to the people that are already high lvls I encourage you to check it out. Give it a shot, it is great fun, especially when you have friends on your team and even more so when you have friends on the opposite team **cough** XxsagexX **cough**. <br /> <br />Well have a good day all. </p>
