		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform2" ><span class="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=399528"><span id="Sage">Wondroustremor</span></a><b><span id="Sage"><br>Sage</span></b><br /><img alt="Avatar" height="100" width="100" src="/uf/Wondroustremor/Galka_Claus.JPG"><br /><br /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><br />787 posts
		   <br /><nobr><span class="notbold">Score</span>: Good [4.38]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Wondroustremor&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%">
<p>Chevy/Chrislee (I need to get used to your original name... still used to Chris), <br /> <br />Thanks for the post.&nbsp;&nbsp;I've done one Ballista before (with my in-game buddy, Inkubus).  We didn't realise it at the time, but we went up against a veteran team in a level 30 cap Ballista in Passhow.  There were 2 people subbing NIN, 1 MNK/THF, 1 BLM, and 2 BSTs with tiger jug pets.  They also had a couple of people with really good ranged attack, and sleep bolts. <br /> <br />Our team was a motley crew of mostly first-time newbies, who weren't even used to not having auto-target (i.e.- you have to lock on the target yourself). <br /> <br />The other team was so organised that they picked us off one at a time, usually 6 on 1 or 7 on 1 (including the pets) while someone else acted as a rabbit to draw away the other members of our team.  I felt confident whenever I went 1-on-1 with the others, as I got my kill first- but I rarely got that opportunity, as they liked to recreate the 'Oz' gang-shower-scene thing whenever they could.  <img border="0" src="/shared/smilies/bah.gif" alt="icon"/>  <br /> <br />Anyway, at the end of our vicious beating, the other team didn't even speak, even when some of us tried to show some showmanship and tell them <span style="color: lime;">{</span>Good job!<span style="color: red;">}</span>.  The only one who did was the BLM, who sent me a /tell saying I should try again some time. <br /> <br />Needless to say, it turned me &amp; Ink right off of Ballista- I just kind of figured that must be how Ballistas are. However, I'd be willing to try a lvl 30 cap again since you said how much fun it is.  It's always nice to get another opinion.  <img border="0" src="/shared/smilies/smile.gif" alt="icon"/> </p>
